name: Nirmala Hotel & Convention Center
address: Jl. Mahendradatta No.81, Padangsambian, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80119, Indonesia
review 1: Great hotel and also have swimming pool for childern great
review 2: The hotel seems old but comfortable enough. Furniture and toilet are old but still work just fine. When I stayed there I paid 200k/night and got breakfast also such as fried fice/fried noodles delivered to room. The staff are also nice and friendly.
review 3: The place is having a simple Balinese home,which I enjoyed the moment. However, they need to fix some parts of the room, because mine was having many troubles like one of the floors was shaky like it's going to fall, The hot water took time to come out, The bathtub was not that clean, The bathroom was quite slippery because they only provided one doormat for it, The floorhinge was the worst. It broke but they didn't fix it. However, The receptionist was super friendly, she was really helpful and nice. The bellboys were great but they didn't have special carriage for luggages. The breakfast was great because it was in a big portion. They could take it to your room. They have a mini market on the first floor that sold many helpful stuffs.
review 4: The bathroom sucks. There's an opened bottle of beer in the bottom cabinet which leaves stinky smell, dirty floor, hot water takes time, the toilet seat is awfully disconnected. Can't turn on the TV. The desk is dusty. The room's colors are terribly limited. Room gives off bad vibe. Can't really be covered by the fortunately nice customer service.
review 5: Quite spacey room but the cleaness is really poor. The floor is dirty and mostly the bathroom is really awfull. There is no cover for drainase hole so smells like seawer. All the tiles full of dirt and spotted, all the wooden is broken and fungus. I must open the tab for 5-10 minutes for hotwater.

name: Rumah Makan Balenong
address: Jl. Mahendradatta No. 49X %28Cargo Permai%29 - Denpasar Padang Sambian Kaja Denpasar Selatan, Padangsambian, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80119, Indonesia
review 1:
I discovered RM Balenong one day while stopping at the red light in front of the place. Not knowing the name of the place, the aroma from the curry was so enticing that I had to search for the restaurant on Google Maps.

Boy was I in for a treat, I ordered for delivery and the food exceeded all of my expectations. Food was tasty, portion was large and the price was very reasonable. The food arrived warm with all of the sides expected of Padang food.

My friend and I have ordered almost 3 times a week and even try dining in. Can definitely recommend to anyone who likes Nasi Padang.
review 2:
Due to renovation, they moved across the street. Bigger space for car parking.

Well, food is so so. Average but not that bad. Taste like any other Padang food, so nothing special. Tad salty and expect oily food.
Also, decent price. Spent 55k because I ordered chicken and prawns.

The place isn't the cleanest so just close your eyes and enjoy the food.
No aircon, open air concept so expect the get some cigarettes blown to your face.

review 1:
This place was previously a noodle restaurant and reopened a noodle restaurant with a different name.
Interesting...
The atmosphere hasn't changed much...

As for the noodles, the texture of the noodles here is quite different from similar restaurant noodles. This characteristic will be a differentiator for sale in the market.

Maybe you can add some sweet noodles?

The variety of drinks is quite interesting, maybe if you can add Ice Macha?

The quality of the side dishes is good.

Live music? Good. Maybe every week held would be interesting.

Thank you for reopening this place.
review 2:
Atmosphere is casual but well appointed, makes me feel like what ever they going to serve me is going to be good.

And the food served here is good, the selections are staggering, my imagination of all the possible flavors don't know where to start or when it will end. It's one of those places where I can blindfold myself and still trust what ever I pointed on the menu is going to taste delicious

name: KANDARA GARDEN CAFE
address: Jl. Buana Raya No.22 C, Padangsambian, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80117, Indonesia
review 1:
Trying this newly open place as it is very close to home.

Venue was fine, it has outdoor seatings or indoor AC room.

Menu has many English typos (mistakes) like Oslo for Coleslaw.

Food options were very limited (but maybe because its just open for a week). Ordered Nasi Goreng, Oxtail Soup, Chicken steak. All the food came out just luke warm not hot. My oxtail soup was very bland had to add more salt and on a bit of the expensive side. Chicken steak was fine, but the vegetables, sauce and wedges were not hot.

No alcoholic beverages options.

Staff were friendly, and helpful.

Overall it was okay, but the foods need improvement.
review 2: Kandara Garden Cafe is a delightful haven where you can indulge in delicious food while immersing yourself in the serene beauty of a lush green garden. Nestled in the heart of the city, this cafe offers not only ample seating but also a dedicated parking area for your convenience. What sets it apart is its unique provision of an indoor space for meetings and co-working, catering to the needs of professionals seeking a tranquil yet productive environment. Moreover, Kandara Garden Cafe is thoughtfully located adjacent to one of Bali's largest indoor playgrounds, The Peekaboo Reborns, ensuring that children can revel in their own expansive play area while parents savor a cup of perfectly brewed coffee or tea. Without a doubt, this enchanting destination beckons visitors to return time and again.
review 3: The service was not satisfactory, I ordered food and it turned out it wasn't entered into the system, even though we had been waiting for a very long time.  disappointing
